args: Hmmm... What color should I use next?\nThe original's blending is pretty subtle...
Hey, Fleur. Have you made any\nbreakthroughs?
I've basically made zero progress!\nHee hee!
You sound surprisingly happy about that.
Well duh! I don't have time to be\ngetting down.
If I don't know what I'm actually aiming\nfor, all I can do is put paint to canvas\nand see what happens.
Art doesn't make itself, you know?\nEspecially the groundbreaking stuff.
You have a point there. What are you\npainting at the moment?
I figured I'd try copying something\nfrom one of the books Elisanne let\nme borrow.
If I wanna incorporate human\nstyles into my art, I need to\nstudy them closely.
So I'm going back to basics—it's great!
Hmm, I see. Sylvans probably don't paint\ntoo much church imagery.
That's a good idea, Fleur.\nI admire your dedication.
Hee hee, thanks!\nIt's not going super well, though.
Really? It looks pretty great to me.
I tried my best to paint it just like\na human would.
But I dunno... It's not quite right.
The original is super cool and stylish\nand ELEGANT—mine looks all kiddy!
Oh? Let me get a better look.
If you have any feedback, just give it\nto me straight! I can take it.
Well, you're right that it doesn't have\nthe same feel as the original.
Yours is different...but in a good way.\nIt's got a real energy to it.
Yeah. The original is beautiful,\nbut I really like your take on it.
The colors are vivid, but the way\nthey're blended is soft and relaxed.
This Ilia makes me think of\na goddess of flowers.
Hmm... I do paint flowers pretty often,\nbut this was meant to be Ilia...
I think the work you've done to date\nis coming out in this piece too.
You might not have realized it, but you've\ndeveloped a signature style.
So when you try to paint something\ntraditionally human, you can't help\nbut refract it through that style.
I've seen a lot of images of Ilia,\nbut never one like this.
Does that mean...I created something\ntotally new?
Seems to me this is exactly the fusion\nyou were going for, don't you think?
I finally found what I was looking for.
I think you may have found it a while\nago, actually.
Why don't you look over the rest\nof the paintings you've done since\ncoming here?
I used human paints to make this one.
And here, I tried to paint a human town\nlike I was painting leaves.
This one was supposed to be a copy\nof a human painting, but I messed up.
I guess there's something sylvan about\neach of them... But do you think\nthey count as fusions?
Each one combines elements\nof sylvan and human culture in\ndifferent ways.
And as long as you keep painting,\nI think you'll find infinite potential\nfor your fusions.
Infinite fusion potential...\nThat sounds so cool!
I guess I really did it after all. Hee hee!
No time to celebrate though—I have to\nkeep pushing!
I've come a long way, but I know\nI can go way further.
I'm looking forward to seeing what\nyou come up with.
OH! Is that... Yes! Inspiration strikes!
Did you think up your next painting?
That's right—I wanna paint a picture\nof the prince that let me live and learn\nat his castle. So let's collaborate!
